  nickname: jas
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: GreetingTesting of Your Faith'
      title: GreetingTesting of Your Faith
      number: 1
      content: '    James, a servant[[COMMENT(0)]] of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ,To
        the twelve tribes in the Dispersion:Greetings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: For the contextual rendering of the Greek word , see Preface
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Count it all joy, my brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]] when you meet trials
        of various kinds, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: "Or . In New Testament usage, depending on the context, the plural
          Greek word (translated \u201Cbrothers\u201D) may refer either to or to
          ; also verses 16, 19"
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'for you know that the testing of your faith produces steadfastness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And let steadfastness have its full effect, that you may be perfect
        and complete, lacking in nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  If any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask God, who gives generously
        to all without reproach, and it will be given him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But let him ask in faith, with no doubting, for the one who doubts
        is like a wave of the sea that is driven and tossed by the wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For that person must not suppose that he will receive anything from
        the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'he is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let the lowly brother boast in his exaltation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and the rich in his humiliation, because like a flower of the grass[[COMMENT(0)]]
        he will pass away. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the sun rises with its scorching heat and withers the grass;
        its flower falls, and its beauty perishes. So also will the rich man fade
        away in the midst of his pursuits.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Blessed is the man who remains steadfast under trial, for when
        he has stood the test he will receive the crown of life, which God has promised
        to those who love him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Let no one say when he is tempted, \u201CI am being tempted by God,\u201D
        for God cannot be tempted with evil, and he himself tempts no one. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But each person is tempted when he is lured and enticed by his own
        desire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then desire when it has conceived gives birth to sin, and sin when
        it is fully grown brings forth death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do not be deceived, my beloved brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down
        from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow due
        to change.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '18: Hearing and Doing the Word'
      title: Hearing and Doing the Word
      number: 18
      content: 'Of his own will he brought us forth by the word of truth, that we
        should be a kind of firstfruits of his creatures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Know this, my beloved brothers: let every person be quick to hear,
        slow to speak, slow to anger; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'for the anger of man does not produce the righteousness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore put away all filthiness and rampant wickedness and receive
        with meekness the implanted word, which is able to save your souls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But be doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For if anyone is a hearer of the word and not a doer, he is like
        a man who looks intently at his natural face in a mirror. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For he looks at himself and goes away and at once forgets what he
        was like. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But the one who looks into the perfect law, the law of liberty, and
        perseveres, being no hearer who forgets but a doer who acts, he will be blessed
        in his doing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "If anyone thinks he is religious and does not bridle his tongue but
        deceives his heart, this person\u2019s religion is worthless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Religion that is pure and undefiled before God the Father is this:
        to visit orphans and widows in their affliction, and to keep oneself unstained
        from the world.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sin of Partiality'
      title: The Sin of Partiality
      number: 1
      content: '  My brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]]  show no partiality as you hold the
        faith in our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Or ; also verses 5, 14
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if a man wearing a gold ring and fine clothing comes into your
        assembly, and a poor man in shabby clothing also comes in, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and if you pay attention to the one who wears the fine clothing and
        say, \u201CYou sit here in a good place,\u201D while you say to the poor
        man, \u201CYou stand over there,\u201D or, \u201CSit down at my feet,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'have you not then made distinctions among yourselves and become judges
        with evil thoughts? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Listen, my beloved brothers, has not God chosen those who are poor
        in the world to be rich in faith and heirs of the kingdom, which he has promised
        to those who love him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But you have dishonored the poor man. Are not the rich the ones who
        oppress you, and the ones who drag you into court? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Are they not the ones who blaspheme the honorable name by which you
        were called?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If you really fulfill the royal law according to the Scripture, \u201CYou
        shall love your neighbor as yourself,\u201D you are doing well. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But if you show partiality, you are committing sin and are convicted
        by the law as transgressors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For whoever keeps the whole law but fails in one point has become
        guilty of all of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For he who said, \u201CDo not commit adultery,\u201D also said, \u201CDo
        not murder.\u201D If you do not commit adultery but do murder, you have become
        a transgressor of the law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So speak and so act as those who are to be judged under the law of
        liberty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Faith Without Works Is Dead'
      title: Faith Without Works Is Dead
      number: 13
      content: 'For judgment is without mercy to one who has shown no mercy. Mercy
        triumphs over judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'What good is it, my brothers, if someone says he has faith but does
        not have works? Can that faith save him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If a brother or sister is poorly clothed and lacking in daily food, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and one of you says to them, \u201CGo in peace, be warmed and filled,\u201D
        without giving them the things needed for the body, what good[[COMMENT(0)]]
        is that? "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So also faith by itself, if it does not have works, is dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But someone will say, \u201CYou have faith and I have works.\u201D
        Show me your faith apart from your works, and I will show you my faith by
        my works. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You believe that God is one; you do well. Even the demons believe\u2014and
        shudder! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do you want to be shown, you foolish person, that faith apart from
        works is useless? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Was not Abraham our father justified by works when he offered up
        his son Isaac on the altar? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You see that faith was active along with his works, and faith was
        completed by his works; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and the Scripture was fulfilled that says, \u201CAbraham believed
        God, and it was counted to him as righteousness\u201D\u2014and he was called
        a friend of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You see that a person is justified by works and not by faith alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And in the same way was not also Rahab the prostitute justified by
        works when she received the messengers and sent them out by another way? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For as the body apart from the spirit is dead, so also faith apart
        from works is dead.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Taming the Tongue'
      title: Taming the Tongue
      number: 1
      content: '    Not many of you should become teachers, my brothers, for you
        know that we who teach will be judged with greater strictness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For we all stumble in many ways. And if anyone does not stumble in
        what he says, he is a perfect man, able also to bridle his whole body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If we put bits into the mouths of horses so that they obey us, we
        guide their whole bodies as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Look at the ships also: though they are so large and are driven by
        strong winds, they are guided by a very small rudder wherever the will of
        the pilot directs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So also the tongue is a small member, yet it boasts of great things.How
        great a forest is set ablaze by such a small fire! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the tongue is a fire, a world of unrighteousness. The tongue
        is set among our members, staining the whole body, setting on fire the entire
        course of life,[[COMMENT(0)]] and set on fire by hell.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: 'Or Greek '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For every kind of beast and bird, of reptile and sea creature, can
        be tamed and has been tamed by mankind, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but no human being can tame the tongue. It is a restless evil, full
        of deadly poison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'With it we bless our Lord and Father, and with it we curse people
        who are made in the likeness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'From the same mouth come blessing and cursing. My brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        these things ought not to be so. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:10 '
        content: Or ; also verse 12
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Does a spring pour forth from the same opening both fresh and salt
        water? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Wisdom from Above'
      title: Wisdom from Above
      number: 12
      content: 'Can a fig tree, my brothers, bear olives, or a grapevine produce
        figs? Neither can a salt pond yield fresh water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who is wise and understanding among you? By his good conduct let
        him show his works in the meekness of wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But if you have bitter jealousy and selfish ambition in your hearts,
        do not boast and be false to the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This is not the wisdom that comes down from above, but is earthly,
        unspiritual, demonic. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For where jealousy and selfish ambition exist, there will be disorder
        and every vile practice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the wisdom from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle,
        open to reason, full of mercy and good fruits, impartial and sincere. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And a harvest of righteousness is sown in peace by those who make
        peace.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Against Worldliness'
      title: Warning Against Worldliness
      number: 1
      content: '  What causes quarrels and what causes fights among you? Is it not
        this, that your passions[[COMMENT(0)]] are at war within you?  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: 'Greek ; also verse 3Greek '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You desire and do not have, so you murder. You covet and cannot obtain,
        so you fight and quarrel. You do not have, because you do not ask. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You ask and do not receive, because you ask wrongly, to spend it
        on your passions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You adulterous people![[COMMENT(0)]] Do you not know that friendship
        with the world is enmity with God? Therefore whoever wishes to be a friend
        of the world makes himself an enemy of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Or do you suppose it is to no purpose that the Scripture says, \u201CHe
        yearns jealously over the spirit that he has made to dwell in us\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he gives more grace. Therefore it says, \u201CGod opposes the
        proud but gives grace to the humble.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Submit yourselves therefore to God. Resist the devil, and he will
        flee from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands,
        you sinners, and purify your hearts, you double-minded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Be wretched and mourn and weep. Let your laughter be turned to mourning
        and your joy to gloom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will exalt you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Do not speak evil against one another, brothers.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        The one who speaks against a brother or judges his brother, speaks evil against
        the law and judges the law. But if you judge the law, you are not a doer
        of the law but a judge. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: Boasting About Tomorrow'
      title: Boasting About Tomorrow
      number: 12
      content: 'There is only one lawgiver and judge, he who is able to save and
        to destroy. But who are you to judge your neighbor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Come now, you who say, \u201CToday or tomorrow we will go into such
        and such a town and spend a year there and trade and make a profit\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'yet you do not know what tomorrow will bring. What is your life?
        For you are a mist that appears for a little time and then vanishes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Instead you ought to say, \u201CIf the Lord wills, we will live and
        do this or that.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'As it is, you boast in your arrogance. All such boasting is evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So whoever knows the right thing to do and fails to do it, for him
        it is sin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning to the Rich'
      title: Warning to the Rich
      number: 1
      content: '  Come now, you rich, weep and howl for the miseries that are coming
        upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Your riches have rotted and your garments are moth-eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your gold and silver have corroded, and their corrosion will be evidence
        against you and will eat your flesh like fire. You have laid up treasure
        in the last days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, the wages of the laborers who mowed your fields, which you
        kept back by fraud, are crying out against you, and the cries of the harvesters
        have reached the ears of the Lord of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You have lived on the earth in luxury and in self-indulgence. You
        have fattened your hearts in a day of slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Patience in Suffering'
      title: Patience in Suffering
      number: 6
      content: 'You have condemned and murdered the righteous person. He does not
        resist you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Be patient, therefore, brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]] until the coming of
        the Lord. See how the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the earth, being
        patient about it, until it receives the early and the late rains. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: Or ; also verses 9, 10, 12, 19
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You also, be patient. Establish your hearts, for the coming of the
        Lord is at hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not grumble against one another, brothers, so that you may not
        be judged; behold, the Judge is standing at the door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As an example of suffering and patience, brothers, take the prophets
        who spoke in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, we consider those blessed who remained steadfast. You have
        heard of the steadfastness of Job, and you have seen the purpose of the Lord,
        how the Lord is compassionate and merciful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Prayer of Faith'
      title: The Prayer of Faith
      number: 12
      content: "But above all, my brothers, do not swear, either by heaven or by
        earth or by any other oath, but let your \u201Cyes\u201D be yes and your
        \u201Cno\u201D be no, so that you may not fall under condemnation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Is anyone among you suffering? Let him pray. Is anyone cheerful?
        Let him sing praise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Is anyone among you sick? Let him call for the elders of the church,
        and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the prayer of faith will save the one who is sick, and the Lord
        will raise him up. And if he has committed sins, he will be forgiven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore, confess your sins to one another and pray for one another,
        that you may be healed. The prayer of a righteous person has great power
        as it is working.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Elijah was a man with a nature like ours, and he prayed fervently
        that it might not rain, and for three years and six months it did not rain
        on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then he prayed again, and heaven gave rain, and the earth bore its
        fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My brothers, if anyone among you wanders from the truth and someone
        brings him back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: let him know that whoever brings back a sinner from his wandering
        will save his soul from death and will cover a multitude of sins.
      comments: []
